{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nOne plan defect currently mints up to N blocking findings via multi-criterion co-citation (ticket a879: two nonexistent symbols x five criteria = 10 blocking findings per round for 3 consecutive rounds; ticket c9d8 round 1: one underspecified escape-hatch surfaced as 4 blocking findings). Agents face an inflated block wall for a single fix-unit, and per-criterion block tallies are distorted for future calibration. Dedup must GROUP, never drop: the gate's strength is unchanged. NOTE: the existing `norm_id` in src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py is criterion-SCOPED (its hash bakes in the sorted criteria list), so norm_id equality CANNOT group across criteria - a criteria-free key is required.\n\n## What\n- Add a `fix_unit_key(finding)` helper in src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py, next to the norm_id machinery: `sha256(norm_location(finding) + \"|\" + norm_claim(finding))`, where norm_claim applies the same token-set normalization norm_id uses on the finding text (reusing its stop-token filtering) but EXCLUDES the criteria list from the hash basis. Same reword tolerance, criteria-free.\n- After verdict production and before the sidecar emit (the seam in src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py where the rising/completion floors already run), group blocking findings sharing a fix_unit_key. Surface ONE primary blocking finding per group (highest priority), carrying members[] (the folded findings) and the union of co-criteria; folded findings keep decision=block in the sidecar (calibration data lossless) and gain a `group_id` field (= the fix_unit_key) so replay can join groups.\n- Sidecar persistence: `build_payload`'s `_slim()` field-selection currently omits unknown fields - explicitly add `group_id` to the `_slim()` dict in sidecar.py so the group key survives into the persisted payload (additive optional field on the current plan-review sidecar schema).\n- CLI renders the primary with a \"(+N co-criteria: E4, G1G2, ...)\" suffix (src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py).\n- Keep the change out of src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/decide.py: this is a pipeline-layer grouping, not a decision change.\n\n## Scope\nIN: fix_unit_key helper, grouping of BLOCKING findings only, group_id persistence through _slim()/build_payload, CLI rendering, tests. OUT: advisory grouping (the advisory cap already bounds volume), cross-round dedup (that is the rising floor's job), any threshold/posture change, any change to norm_id itself.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A synthetic verdict with 5 blocking findings citing the same location and same claim text across 5 different criteria surfaces exactly 1 primary blocking finding with 4 members and the 5-criteria union; the verdict remains BLOCK. Oracle: new unit test; `python -m pytest tests/unit -k \"fix_unit or dedup\" -x` green.\n- [ ] Findings at different locations or with different claims are NOT grouped, and two findings with identical text but different criteria ARE grouped (the criteria-free key property). Oracle: unit tests over fix_unit_key asserting both directions.\n- [ ] The emitted sidecar retains all 5 findings with decision=block, each carrying the same group_id. Oracle: unit test reads the build_payload output and asserts 5 block-decision findings sharing one group_id.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` all pass."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784093147746564001,"uuid":"487cbe2e-70ad-4329-9590-3318bf358479"}